items.title: Awesome Zsh Plugins
items.content_text:
### Plugins / [superconsole](https://github.com/alexchmykhalo/superconsole) - Windows-only

*   [get-jquery (‚≠ê1)](https://github.com/voronkovich/get-jquery.plugin.zsh) - Plugin for fast downloading the jQuery library from [code.jquery.com](https://code.jquery.com).
*   [gtm-terminal-plugin (‚≠ê16)](https://github.com/git-time-metric/gtm-terminal-plugin) - terminal plugin for [git time metrics (‚≠ê994)](https://github.com/git-time-metric/gtm).

### Completions / [superconsole](https://github.com/alexchmykhalo/superconsole) - Windows-only

*   [brew-services (‚≠ê19)](https://github.com/vasyharan/zsh-brew-services) - Completion plugin for [homebrew](https://brew.sh) services.
*   [buidler (‚≠ê3)](https://github.com/gonzalobellino/buidler-zsh) - Adds completion and useful aliases for NomicLabs Buidler tool.
*   [ipfs (‚≠ê9)](https://github.com/hellounicorn/zsh-ipfs) - Completions for the [Interplanetary File System](https://ipfs.tech).
*   [keybase (‚≠ê19)](https://github.com/rbirnie/oh-my-zsh-keybase) - Completions for [keybase](https://book.keybase.io/docs/cli).
*   [kubeadm (‚≠ê4)](https://github.com/gantsign/zsh-plugins/tree/master/kubeadm) - Add tab completions for [kubeadm](https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/setup-tools/kubeadm/).

### Themes / [superconsole](https://github.com/alexchmykhalo/superconsole) - Windows-only

*   [astro (‚≠ê106)](https://github.com/iplaces/astro-zsh-theme) - Based on the `ys` and [robbyrussell (‚≠ê180k)](https://github.com/ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh/wiki/Themes#robbyrussell) themes.
*   [emojeer (‚≠ê0)](https://github.com/lxynox/emojeer-ohmyzsh) - Emoji flavored [oh-my-zsh](https://ohmyz.sh/) theme.
*   [pedantic (‚≠ê0)](https://github.com/nemeshnorbert/pedantic-zsh-theme) - Customizable colors and output. Includes decorators for detailed `git` information, root status, last command's exit status, user\@host, current directory and the time.
*   [stigmata (‚≠ê0)](https://github.com/VLtim43/stigmata.zsh-theme) - Includes decorators for user\@host and current directory.
